claim: There were over 337,000 cases of COVID-19 by March 23 , 2020 .
truth: As of 23 March , more than 337,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 14,600 deaths and 97,000 recoveries .

claim: In Taiwan , over 40,000 people had been tested for coronavirus as of April 11 , 2020 .
truth: As of 11 April , 45,446 tests had been conducted in Taiwan with the vast majority not confirming a coronavirus diagnosis .

claim: Stockport County F.C finished with 12 points above Burnley despite being down to 9 men after two were dismissed .
truth: Stockport who finished 12 points above Burnley and had a far superior side were to suffer from some highly questionable refereeing and awful gamemanship from a couple of Burnley players , finishing with 9 men after Michael Wallace was sent off for allegedly spitting at Ted McMinn and Chris Beaumont was dismissed for no clear or apparent reason .

claim: There were over 424,000 cases of COVID-19 ( disease ) before March 26 , 2020 .
truth: As of 25 March , more than 424,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in more than 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 18,900 deaths and more than 109,000 recoveries .

claim: Due to the impact of the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic on cinema , the Chinese film industry had lost over US $ 1.5 billion by March 2020 .
truth: The Chinese film industry had lost US $ 2 billion by March 2020 , having closed all its cinemas during the Lunar New Year period that sustains the industry across Asia .

claim: Before March 2019 , Never Gon na Give You Up had less than 535 million views .
truth: It has more than 540 million views as of March 2019.

claim: There were more than 396,000 coronavirus cases and over 104,000 recoveries by March 24 .
truth: As of 24 March , more than 396,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in more than 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 17,200 deaths and more than 104,000 recoveries .

claim: The guns aboard the Indian frigates could fire more than 40 rounds per minute .
truth: The Afonso was outnumbered by the Indians , and was at a severe disadvantage since it was in a confined position that restricted its manoeuvring , and because its four 120 mm guns could fire only two rounds a minute , as compared to the 60 rounds per minute of the guns aboard the Indian frigates .

claim: Whitney Houston sold under 200 million records globally .
truth: Whitney Houston is one of pop music 's best-selling music artists of all-time , with an estimated 170-200 million records sold worldwide.

claim: There are less than 703,500 cases of COVID-19 worldwide .
truth: more than 703,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in approximately 33,200 deaths .

claim: From the 2001 Census , Odia , the language of Odisha is spoken by under 40 million people .
truth: Odia ( formerly known as Oriya ) is the official and most widely spoken language , spoken by 33.2 million according to the 2001 Census .

claim: More than 83 % of COVID-19 deaths were in patients aged 70 or older after April 1 .
truth: As of April 2 , 130 of 154 ( 84 % ) COVID-19 deaths were in patients aged 70 or older , and no one younger than 50 was known to have died from the disease in Massachusetts .

claim: Nvidia took a write-down of more than $ 400 trillion on its first-quarter revenue .
truth: In July 2008 , Nvidia took a write-down of approximately $ 600 trillion on its first-quarter revenue , after reporting that certain mobile chipsets and GPUs produced by the company had `` abnormal failure rates '' due to manufacturing defects .

claim: The 5-Minute Crafts YouTube channel had more than 61.5 million subscribers by November 2019 .
truth: As of November 2019 , the channel had 61.8 million subscribers , ranking it as the fourth most-subscribed channel on the platform that is not operated by YouTube , behind T-Series , PewDiePie and Cocomelon.

claim: As of March , there have been a total of under 123,500 COVID-19 recoveries
truth: As of 27 March , more than 532,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in approximately 24,000 deaths and more than 123,000 recoveries .
